## Navbar icons

Find out what icons you can choose from to use in the navbar [here](https://icons.getbootstrap.com/)

## Themes

-   You can either use one of the bootstrap themes, or make a custom.scss

-   Find the bootstrap themes [here](https://bootswatch.com/)

-   You can have a dark and a light theme by putting this in the \_quarto.yml:

``` r
format:
  html:
    theme: 
      light: minty
      dark: cyborg
```

### Custom.scss

To create a custom.scss file, create a new text file and name it custom.scss

#### Useful SASS variables

+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| Variable name             | What it does                                                       | Example                           |
+===========================+====================================================================+===================================+
| `$body-bg`                | Page background colour                                             | `$body-bg: #eac891;`              |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$body-color`             | Page text colour                                                   | `$body-color: black;`             |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$link-color`             | Link colour                                                        | `$link-color: #3B7A57;`           |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$font-family-sans-serif` | Text font for the page                                             | `$font-family-sans-serif: Cardo;` |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$font-size-root`         | Font size                                                          | `$font-size-root: 0.9am;`         |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$h1-font-size`           | Font sizes for headers                                             | `$h1-font-size: 2am;`             |
|                           |                                                                    |                                   |
| `$h2-font-size`           |                                                                    |                                   |
|                           |                                                                    |                                   |
| `$h3-font-size`           |                                                                    |                                   |
|                           |                                                                    |                                   |
| `$h4-font-size`           |                                                                    |                                   |
|                           |                                                                    |                                   |
| `$h5-font-size`           |                                                                    |                                   |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$code-bg:`               | Inline code background (like the code in the variable name column) | `$code-bg: #3B7A57;`              |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$code-color`             | Inline code colour                                                 | `$code-color: white;`             |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$navbar-bg`              | Navbar (top of page) background colour                             | `$navbar-bg: #ae431e;`            |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$navbar-fg`              | Navbar foreground (text and icons in navbar) colour                | `$navbar-fg: white;`              |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$navbar-hl`              | Highlight colour for links in navbar                               | `$navbar-hl: black;`              |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$sidebar-bg`             | Sidebar background                                                 | `$sidebar-bg: #d06224;`           |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$sidebar-fg`             | Sidebar foreground                                                 | `$sidebar-fg: white;`             |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| `$sidebar-hl`             | Sidebar highlight                                                  | `$sidebar-hl: black;`             |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+

[Here](https://quarto.org/docs/output-formats/html-themes.html#theme-options) is a list of all the useful SASS variables you might need

Look at the scss files for bootswatch themes [here](https://github.com/bum/bootstrap-color/blob/master/bootswatch/cerulean/_variables.scss)

Here are two useful videos on how to style Quarto docs without knowing CSS or HTML:

1.  [Video 1](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jX4_Dnzhl0M&list=PLBnFxG6owe1FnrefMnzEcIxePF1SEKpPy)
2.  [Video 2](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QU8wSya-Y9E&list=PLBnFxG6owe1FnrefMnzEcIxePF1SEKpPy&index=4) - this video explains how to inspect your rendered document and edit the HTML code to make your document look exactly how you want it to

#### Example custom.scss doc:

``` scss
/*-- scss:defaults --*/
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto|Bebas+Neue|Kanit|Anton|Acme|Merriweather');

// colours
$green-1: #cad2c5;
$green-2: #84a98c;
$green-3: #52796f;
$green-4: #354f52;
$green-5: #2f3e46;



// body colours
$body-bg: white;
$body-color: black;
$link-color: $green-3; 

// fonts
$font-family-sans-serif: "Roboto", "Open Sans", "Cambria", "Georgia", "serif";

// inline code colours
$code-bg: $green-3;
$code-color: white;

// navbar 
$navbar-bg: $green-2;
$navbar-fg: white;
$navbar-hl: black; 

// sidebar
$sidebar-bg: $green-3;



/*-- scss:rules --*/


h1, .h1, h2, .h2, h3, .h3, h4, .h4, h5, .h5 {
    color: #52796f;
    font-family: "Merriweather";
}
```

### Using custom.scss in your \_quarto.yml

``` r
format:
  html:
    theme:
       light: custom.scss
       dark: dark.scss
```
